      "image": "/images/dragon-ears.png"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "07-a-solid-plan_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "07 - A Solid Plan",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "10",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "07-a-solid-plan_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "The party aimed to raid the cellar beneath Adsuren Center, their strongest lead on the cult, while deflecting blame for the missing town taxes. Esylla found Mollywop oddly exhausted. They planted stolen gold in Ganon's boarding house to get the guards off their trail. They descended into the cellar that night, proving it to be the hideout they were hoping to find. They found cultists and evidence of their rituals using hearts and black salt. Descending deeper and disposing of more cultists, the session ended at a set of double doors deep beneath Adsuren.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "11",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "07-a-solid-plan_recording_1",
    "type": "media-player",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 07 Recording",
      "src": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_yWZston6bYsRlP6lSrO59-HLoMK9Caj/view?usp=sharing",
      "mediaType": "auto",
      "caption": "",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "12",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "2",
      "displayMode": "image-button",
      "image": "/images/dragon-ears.png"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "06-who-took-it_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "06 - Who Took It?",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "14",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "06-who-took-it_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "The party set out from Mollywop's tower determined to uncover the location of the rituals plaguing Adsuren and this Summoner Karranock. The heart-harvesting rites were taking place somewhere deeper in town. The day unfolded with tavern intrigue, dockside questioning, and a tense search of Ganon's rented room that revealed twitching rat heads and precise instructions for creating black salt from sentient hearts. Kenton added his own complications by quietly lifting tax pouches from the Adsuren Center, an act that quickly turned the town's Market Day preparations into a flurry of guarded suspicion. By session's end the Souls of Destiny found themselves chasing a shadowy cult while trying not to trip over the fresh chaos one of their own had sown.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "15",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "06-who-took-it_recording_1",
    "type": "media-player",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 06 Recording",
      "src": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1bZuRvD9TeZ1z22PHqzqUTquIXYR8FndI/view?usp=sharing",
      "mediaType": "auto",
      "caption": "",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "16",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "2",
      "displayMode": "image-button",
      "image": "/images/dragon-ears.png"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "05-thugs-and-cultists_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "05 - Thugs & Cultists",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "18",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "05-thugs-and-cultists_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "The party set out to track the shadowy cult responsible for poisoning Adsuren's well. Most of the group interrogated the local tanner and battled his cultist apprentice Ganon. However, Kenton was ambushed in an alley by thugs led by Sir Rodolf Norran from Gibuldon. Rodolf left behind a healing potion marked \"Ryvennra\" after Kenton fell. The party then consulted Mollywop the Magnificent, who identified the cult's lesser fiendish amulet and unholy black salt, and used Speak with Dead to learn that Summoner Karranock leads the group and their outdoor rituals occur somewhere deeper in Adsuren. Now aware that an imp may have alerted the cult, the heroes must carefully flush out their hidden enemies without alarming the village, while also bracing for Rodolf's next move.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "19",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "05-thugs-and-cultists_recording_1",
    "type": "media-player",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 05 Recording",
      "src": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NpK-tNkffM9QkwSv96Jn6kBRE3aSQ69q/view?usp=sharing",
      "mediaType": "auto",
      "caption": "",
