      "row": "24",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "2",
      "displayMode": "image-button",
      "image": "/images/dragon-ears.png"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "03-fungipheliac-using-kinfolk_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "03 - Fungipheliac Using Kinfolk",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "26",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "03-fungipheliac-using-kinfolk_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "The party sought to uncover what had happened to the missing Sapcutt family after being betrayed and trapped beneath their home. Fighting through fungal undead and deadly traps, they discovered the house itself was sustained by a sentient corruption born from something pulled out of the swamp. By rescuing Lobella and learning the grim bargain her mother had made, the party chose to save the living rather than destroy everything in their path. They escaped into the night with the surviving Sapcutts, knowing the true source of the corruption still lurked somewhere beyond the house.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "27",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "03-fungipheliac-using-kinfolk_recording_1",
